d library class. I'm evaluating whether using `createResolvedMethod` with `String.class.getMethod(\\\"substring\\\", int.class)` makes sense, considering JDK reflection and the metadata available. Maybe relying on public API to create ResolvedMember is better to avoid issues with test class reflection? I'm curious if using Class.getMethod on String would still be acceptable.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring metadata schemas**\\n\\nI’m looking to see if any metadata schemas can support a reflection format. There’s quite a bit of information out there, so it’ll be interesting to analyze various examples. I wonder how they approach this concept and which ones are most effective. It might be helpful to compare them to get a clearer picture of their capabilities. I'll aim to gather useful insights and see where I can draw connections!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_LcoPomol9ffKNWgkLs14uyiQ|fc_0e1b3ffae8ddc0360169f17b33de64819fa497f724af034b5a", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg -n '\"reflection\"|\"methods\".*<init>|\"parameterTypes\"' metadata | head -80", "timeout": 10}, "partialJson": "{\"command\":\"rg -n '\\\"reflection\\\"|\\\"methods\\\".*<init>|\\\"parameterTypes\\\"' metadata | head -80\",\"timeout\":10}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1359, "output": 1864, "cacheRead": 36352, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 39575, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777433367688, "responseId": "resp_0e1b3ffae8ddc0360169f17b186c54819f88b83b7777eb6964"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_LcoPomol9ffKNWgkLs14uyiQ|fc_0e1b3ffae8ddc0360169f17b33de64819fa497f724af034b5a", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "metadata/org.mockito/mockito-core/4.8.1/reachability-metadata.json:2:  \"reflection\": [\nmetadata/org.mockito/mockito-core/4.8.1/reachability-metadata.jso